","Elmsall South Kirky West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Elmsall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pollington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name, evidently from Pollington (Yorkshire). The placename derives from an unknown first element + the Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The surname is now mainly found in Sussex, to which it appears to have migrated at an early date from Yorkshire."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":30,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Pollington was born about 1260, his father, Thomas Pollington, was 27 and his mother, Joyce Cave, was 32. He married Isabella Horbury in 1280, in Elmsall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. He died in 1297, in Pollington, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 38."},"et":{"Abt 1260–1297":"umbes 1260–1297","1260–1297":"1260–1297","1260–1302":"12